{"ts":"2026-06-16T22:00:00+00:00","source":"evolve-strategy","mode":"hypothesis","strategy":"vol_target_momentum","baseline":"momentum_12_1","universe":"diversified","params":{"top_n":20,"target_vol":0.3,"vol_window":20,"regime_ma":200,"sizing":"vol_target","split":"2022-06-30"},"splits":[{"name":"IS","start":"2017-01-01","end":"2022-06-30","sharpe":-0.25},{"name":"OOS","start":"2022-07-01","end":"2026-06-16","sharpe":0.359}],"decay":-0.609,"fitness":-0.4,"gate":"reject","hypothesis":"Multi-split check: is the vol-target overlay edge on diversified robust across split boundaries, or regime-luck?","notes":"REJECT for satellite; DOWNGRADES iter-4 tactical. Multi-split reveals regime-dependence: on the 2021-06-30 split the overlay BEAT baseline OOS (+0.278 vs -1.321, OOS contains 2022 crash) but on the 2022-06-30 split it LOSES to baseline (+0.359 vs +0.608, OOS is the recovery). The overlay is a CRASH HEDGE not robust alpha: its regime gate wins when OOS includes a drawdown it sidesteps, loses when OOS is a recovery it sits out. Confirms the deflated-Sharpe caution (iter-4 +0.278 was noise-band). The multi-split gate caught regime-luck a single split would have promoted.","run_id":"2026-06-16T22:00:00+00:00-vol_target_momentum-6382"}
