{"ts":"2026-06-16T22:45:00+00:00","source":"evolve-strategy","mode":"hypothesis","strategy":"momentum_12_1","baseline":"momentum_12_1","universe":"broad","params":{"top_n":20,"rebalance":"monthly","universe_size":200,"sizing":"risk_based"},"splits":[{"name":"IS","start":"2017-01-01","end":"2021-06-30","sharpe":0.75,"cagr":27.725,"exposure":1.07},{"name":"OOS","start":"2021-07-01","end":"2026-06-16","sharpe":-0.322,"cagr":-3.02,"exposure":0.458}],"decay":1.072,"fitness":-1.39,"gate":"reject","hypothesis":"A broad 200-name cross-section fixes the under-deployment that crippled momentum on 12 names and lets it perform","notes":"META-FINDING CONFIRMED but OOS REJECT. Breadth fixed deployment: IS exposure 0.15(watchlist)->1.07(full), IS CAGR +27.7%, IS Sharpe 0.75 (QQQ-like) \u2014 momentum WORKS in-sample when it has a real cross-section. BUT OOS Sharpe -0.322 (decay 1.072) on the 2021-06-30 crash split, AND big CAVEAT: universe built from CURRENTLY-liquid names = survivorship bias (excludes delisted) -> IS is research-grade/inflated (data rule). So breadth is NECESSARY (fixes deployment) but not SUFFICIENT (OOS regime decay + survivorship). Single split. Next: multi-split on broad to see if OOS failure is just the 2022-crash split (cf iter-5).","run_id":"2026-06-16T22:45:00+00:00-momentum_12_1-882f"}
